post_text:
from the providence journal:
"PROVIDENCE –– Education Commissioner Deborah A. Gist is recommending that two existing charter schools be granted five-year renewals based on their strong academic track record, clearing a more rigorous review process developed recently by the state Department of Education.

Blackstone Academy, a high school serving students from Central Falls and Pawtucket, and The Compass School, a K-8 school in South Kingstown, were praised for their strong leadership. Blackstone, which serves some of the poorest students in Rhode Island, was singled out for its impressive improvement in math and reading during the past few years, while Compass School, in South County, consistently ranks among the top public schools in the state."

